The real concern is that the PR's approach of switching to two separate `anySatisfy` calls doesn't guarantee exactly two suppressed exceptions exist—it only confirms each path was attempted at least once. Adding a size check would make this more explicit and catch cases where unexpected exceptions get added later. This is a minor refinement rather than a critical issue, but it would strengthen the test's precision.
